# Append-only state ledgers: union-merge concurrent appends instead of conflicting.
#
# Event-driven + heartbeat-driven runs (SPEC-v4/v5) mean two workflow runs can each
# append a line to the same ledger and both try to push. `git pull --rebase` then hit
# a real "CONFLICT (content)" on these files (observed: a scout-act run failed exactly
# this way). The built-in `union` merge driver keeps BOTH sides' added lines — exactly
# right for append-only JSONL, whose readers dedup by uri/ts and are order-tolerant.
*.jsonl merge=union
